arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)
	Hydra.ActorMergeAIState(idActorSpawned, S_AISTATE_DEFAULT, idActorSpawned, 0)
	Hydra.ActorOverrideAIAwarenessRadius(idActorSpawned, 10, true)
end

function Start(idActorDamager, idActorDamaged)
	
	local npcHealth = Hydra.ActorGetHitPointsPercent(idActorDamaged)
	if npcHealth > 0.35 and npcHealth < 0.90 then
		Hydra.ActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVO_BATTLE_BRAVE, ID_NPC)
	elseif npcHealth < 0.35 then 
		Hydra.ActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVO_BATTLE_FEARFUL, ID_NPC)
	end
end

function Start(idActorKiller, szScopedGroup, PrefabID)
	
	Hydra.Wait(1)
	
	local nWave = UF_GetCurrentWave()
	if nWave <= N_WAVE_COUNT then
		championSpawnCount = 0	-- reset this each time we spawn waves
	
		-- Offset mod since we don't start our indices at 0 in lua
		UF_StartLaneWave((nWave - 1) % #tLaneData + 1, nWave)
		 
		-- lane 4 and 5 spawn a second lane		
		if nWave >= 4 and #tLaneData > 1 then
		
			Hydra.Wait(0.5)
			
			UF_StartLaneWave(nWave % #tLaneData + 1, nWave)
			
		end
		
		-- lane 5 spawns all three lanes
		if nWave >= 5 and #tLaneData > 1 then
		
			Hydra.Wait(0.5)
			
			UF_StartLaneWave((nWave + 1) % #tLaneData + 1, nWave)
			
		end
		-- Spawn the super elite here if we're at the end
		if nWave == N_WAVE_COUNT then
			Events.ActorEnableSpawner(ID_SPAWNER_SUPER)
		end
	end
	
end

arCallbackSets.szOnSetCompleteScript:
Hydra.Wait(1.0)

if Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_NPC) and Hydra.ActorIsAlive(ID_NPC) then
	Hydra.ActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVO_VICTORY, ID_NPC)
end

Hydra.QuestAdvancePhase()

arQuestPhases.szOnEnterScript:
Hydra.ActorEnableAI(ID_NPC, true)
Hydra.ActorSetInvulnerable(ID_NPC, false)

-- give this npc damage reduction when low health to create barely-made-it moments
-- Also adds 75% DOT damage reduction to the NPC, as it feels bad when they just die to poison
Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(DAMAGE_REDUCTION_POWER, "MAIN", ID_NPC)
Hydra.QActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVO_INTROSHOUT, ID_NPC)

FYShuffle(tLaneData)
UF_StartLaneWave(1, 1)

arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorPlayer, sLevelAreaName)
	if sLevelAreaName == S_LEVEL_AREA then
		Hydra.EventSendToActor("PlayerInLevelArea", idSelf, idSelf)
	end
end

function Start()
	if #Hydra.PlayerActorsInLevelArea(S_LEVEL_AREA) > 0 then
		Hydra.EventSendToActor("PlayerInLevelArea", idSelf, idSelf)
	end
end

function Start()
	local sChest = ACTOR_CHEST_REWARD

	if Hydra.QuestGetBonusPhaseResult() then
		sChest = ACTOR_CHEST_REWARD_HEROIC
	end
	
	Events.SpawnRewardChest(CHEST_LOCATION, sChest)
end

arCallbackSets.szOnSetCompleteScript:
if Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_NPC) and Hydra.ActorIsAlive(ID_NPC) then
	Hydra.ActorPlaySimpleConversation(S_CONVO_VICTORY, ID_NPC)
end
Hydra.WaitForConversationFinished(S_CONVO_VICTORY)

szUserFunctionsScript:
function UF_GetCurrentWave()

	return Hydra.QuestCallbackCountGet(7) + 1

end

function UF_StartLaneWave(nLane, nWave)
	
	-- minor wave sfx on 1-3, major wave sfx on 4-5
	local sfx
	if nWave == N_WAVE_COUNT then
		sfx = SFX_MAJOR_WAVE
	else
		sfx = SFX_MINOR_WAVE
	end
	
	-- do spawns and sfx
	local playedSfx = false
	
	for i, idSpawner in pairs(tLaneData[nLane][nWave]) do
	
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idSpawner) then		
			-- only do champs once per spawn wave
			if Hydra.ActorIsInPrefabScopedGroup(idSpawner, PSAG_CHAMPION_SPAWNERS) then 
				if championSpawnCount < maxChampionsPerWave then 
					Events.ActorEnableSpawner(idSpawner)
					championSpawnCount = championSpawnCount + 1
				end
			else
				Events.ActorEnableSpawner(idSpawner)
			end
			
			if playedSfx == false and Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_NPC) then
				Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(ID_NPC, sfx)
				playedSfx = true
			end
		end	
	end	
end
szOnStartupScript:
ID_THIS_QUEST = Hydra.QuestGetOwner()
PSAG_CHAMPION_SPAWNERS = "EH_Champion_Spawner"

-- WT4 = 2 champs possible, WT3 = 1 champ possible
maxChampionsPerWave = (Hydra.GameGetCurrentWorldTier() == Hydra.WORLD_TIER_4 and 2 or 1)
championSpawnCount = 0			

--grab the spawner we want to spawn a super at at the end of the event
local tSpawnerSupers = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Unique_Spawner")
FYShuffle(tSpawnerSupers)

ID_SPAWNER_SUPER = tSpawnerSupers[1]

-- Create a list of lanes depending on how many we find.
tLaneData = {}
repeat

	local nLane = #tLaneData+1
	
	tLaneData[nLane] = 
		{
			Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. nLane .. "_WAVE1"),
			Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. nLane .. "_WAVE2"),
			Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. nLane .. "_WAVE3"),
			Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. nLane .. "_WAVE4"),
			Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. nLane .. "_WAVE5"),
		}
	
	local tNextGroup = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(ID_THIS_QUEST, "SPAWNER_LANE" .. (nLane+1) .. "_WAVE1")
	
until tNextGroup == nil or #tNextGroup <= 0

N_WAVE_COUNT = #tLaneData[1]

Hydra.ActorSetBloody(ID_NPC, Hydra.GetRandomFloat(0.3, 0.6))
Hydra.ActorSetInvulnerable(ID_NPC, true)
Hydra.ActorEnableAI(ID_NPC, false)
Hydra.ActorSetAITether(ID_NPC, ID_TETHER_LOC)
Hydra.ActorMergeAIState(ID_NPC, AISTATE_NPC, ID_NPC, 0)
